  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess retinal nerve fiber layer thickness and macular
      thickness measured with optical coherence tomography (OCT) on patients infected by HIV virus
      without ocular manifestations and to correlate these results with perimetric findings
      assessed by frequency doubling technology perimetry (FDT).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
